<li class="collection__item">
<h2 class="title">Antonio Vivaldi (1678-1741)</h2>
<p class="paragraph-text"><a href="/composers/vivaldi/">Vivaldi</a>, one of the most productive composers of the <a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/baroque/">Baroque</a> era, wrote an astonishing 500 concertos  including the still oft-heard <em>Four Seasons</em>, four <a href="/discover-music/instruments/violin/">violin</a> concertos that each depict one season of the year. </p><p class="paragraph-text">The work is as fresh and colourful today, somehow, as it must have been when it was heard by Vivaldis contemporaries, such was his mastery of melody, harmony and scoring.   </p>
