<h2 class="title">Claude Debussy (1862-1918) </h2>
<p class="paragraph-text">Impressionist master, <a href="/composers/debussy/">Debussy</a>, brought colours to music previously not heard, and his large-scale works like <em>Prlude  laprs midi dune faune</em> helped transform music at the turn of the century.   </p><p class="paragraph-text">The French composer was responsible for the utterly transporting <a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/opera/">opera</a> <em>Pellas et Mlisande</em>, and enduring <a href="/discover-music/instruments/piano/">piano</a> favourite, <em>Clair de Lune</em>.</p><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>Read more: </strong><a href="/composers/debussy/best-pieces-classical-music/"><strong>10 of Claude Debussys greatest pieces of music</strong></a></p>
