<h2 class="title">Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky (1840-1893)</h2>
<p class="paragraph-text">This 19th-century Russian great gave us <em>Swan Lake</em>, <em>The Nutcracker</em> and <em>Sleeping Beauty</em>  and off the ballet stage, epic symphonies and concertos, as well as enduring orchestral works. This includes the <em>1812 Overture</em>, of which <a href="/composers/tchaikovsky/">Tchaikovsky</a> purportedly wasnt as much of a fan, as the whole world since. </p>
