<li class="collection__item">
<h2 class="title">Robert Schumann (18101856)</h2>
<p class="paragraph-text"><a href="/composers/schumann/">Schumann</a>s <a href="/discover-music/instruments/piano/">piano</a> music, chamber music and symphonies were all revolutionary and, picking up the baton from Beethoven, set the tone for the <a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/romantic/">Romantic</a> era in music.</p><p class="paragraph-text">Also a music critic, Schumann co-founded one of the most influential musical publications, the <em>Neue Zeitschrift fr Musik</em>, writing many of the articles himself under the pseudonyms Florestan and Eusebius.</p>
