<li class="collection__item">
<h2 class="title">Richard Wagner (18131883)	</h2>
<p class="paragraph-text">Sticking with opera, and born in the same year as <a href="/composers/verdi/">Verdi</a> (see above) was <a href="/composers/wagner/">Richard Wagner</a>. </p><p class="paragraph-text">Few people contend with this great German composer when it comes to the sheer extent to which he revolutionised the artform. In the 19th century, Wagner created epic operas unmatched in their length and ambition in <em>Tristan und Isolde</em> and <em>The Ring</em> (a cycle of four long operas) among other monumental works.</p><p class="paragraph-text">He built his own opera house, Bayreuth, to host his epic creations and also invented the leitmotif, a musical device that sees certain melodies or themes composed to depict specific characters or ideas  something that would persist in <a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/opera/">opera</a>, and beyond to <a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/film-tv/">film scoring</a>, in works by the likes of <a href="/composers/zimmer/">Hans Zimmer</a> and <a href="/composers/williams/">John Williams</a>. </p>
<div class="video-container">
<div class="video-facade video-facade__brightcove" id="video_facade_brightcove_6065715680001" data-video-provider="brightcove" data-video-id="6065715680001" data-account="6057949401001">
<img src="https://cf-images.eu-west-1.prod.boltdns.net/v1/static/6057949401001/b173207c-507d-44ad-b3f3-cba3b5830966/50ce0fb3-8b8b-4642-b6bd-609853a91624/640x360/match/image.jpg" loading="lazy" />
<div class="title">
<p>Wagner percussion FAIL!</p>
</div>
