<li class="collection__item">
<h2 class="title">Dmitri Shostakovich (1906-1975)</h2>
<p class="paragraph-text">Russian great <a href="/composers/shostakovich/">Shostakovich</a>s career was defined by the Soviet era, and specifically Soviet favour  the Symphony No. 5 was held up as a Stalinist triumph  and then Soviet disapprobation, when he was denounced as decadent and non-patriotic.</p><p class="paragraph-text">He wrote 15 symphonies, numerous operas and ballets, and instrumental and orchestral works, as well as soundtracks for early cinema.</p><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>Read more: </strong><a href="/discover-music/periods-genres/modern/20th-century-best-composers/"><strong>10 of the best 20th-century composers</strong></a></p>
